{"id":297572518,"lang":"python3","time":"1 year, 5 months","timestamp":1580052324,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"5816 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/297572518/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Perfect Squares","memory":"12.9 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def numSquares(self, n):\n        dp = [float(\"inf\") for _ in range(n+1)]\n        dp[0], dp[1] = 0, 1\n        x = 1\n        while x * x <= n:\n            dp[x*x] = 1\n            x += 1\n            \n        for i in range(2, n+1):\n            x = 1\n            while x * x < i:\n                val = x * x\n                dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i-val] + dp[val])\n                x += 1\n        return dp[n]\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"perfect-squares"}
